        <mxCell id="QrUjFgdpP7e0IE09AZfR-4" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=22;" value="EXPERIMENT NO: 10&#xa;Elasticsearch vs PostgreSQL Performance Analysis System Design&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;1. Functional Requirements (FR&#39;s)&#xa;• Search &amp; Discovery: Users must be able to search through 2,000,000 synthetic eCommerce products using partial string (&quot;search-as-you-type&quot;) inputs.&#xa;&#xa;• Comparative Benchmarking: System must execute identical query parameters simultaneously across dual independent data engines (SQL and NoSQL).&#xa;&#xa;• Real-time Metrics: Must accurately capture, analyze, and return independent execution latency metrics down to the millisecond.&#xa;&#xa;• Transparent Initialization: System must automatically seed un-hydrated environments upon startup with synthetic data.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;2. Non-Functional Requirements (NFR&#39;s)&#xa;• Low Latency: Elasticsearch query resolution must inherently return results in &lt;50ms, contrasting directly against relational sequential scan times.&#xa;&#xa;• High Throughput Initialization: The persistence layer must be capable of inserting 2,000,000 records dynamically on standard local hardware.&#xa;&#xa;• Memory Optimization: Database initialization logic must utilize memory-chunking to prevent standard ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) JVM OutOfMemory Exceptions.&#xa;&#xa;• Reliable Port Binding: Independent container orchestration isolated to safe hardware ports (e.g., PostgreSQL targeting port 5434).&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;3. API Design&#xa;• GET /api/compare?query=(q): Core benchmarking endpoint. Broadcasts the query independently to both Elasticsearch and PostgreSQL and measures runtime discrepancy.&#xa;&#xa;• GET /api/stats: Background task tracking endpoint checking bulk-insertion progress.&#xa;&#xa;• GET /: Serves the client-side single-page dashboard mapping REST payloads.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;4. Core Entities&#xa;• Product: Base entity/document mapping identical properties (ID, name, description, brand, category, price, timestamp).&#xa;&#xa;• SearchResult: Localized DTO analyzing speed/latency metrics of an isolated engine.&#xa;&#xa;• ComparisonResult: Aggregation record pairing both data systems over the target 2_000_000 volume for differential visualization.&#xa;&#xa;• Background Stats Engine: Tracks the atomic status of ongoing asynchronous cluster syncing tasks.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;5. Database Schema Design&#xa;• Product Table (PostgreSQL): (id VARCHAR, brand VARCHAR, category VARCHAR, description VARCHAR, name VARCHAR, price FLOAT8, timestamp INT8)&#xa;&#xa;• Inverted Index (Elasticsearch): (index=&quot;products&quot;, mapped grammatical tokens explicitly ignoring unstructured character scans)&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;6. High Level Design (HLD)&#xa;&#xa;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="920" width="810" x="710" y="-1770" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
